KZN cops are still searching for the family of a man who was washed up at Golf Course Beach in Amanzimtoti, south of Durban.Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane, KZN cops spokesman, said: &ldquo;Police divers and the search and rescue unit were called on Monday afternoon to recover the body of an unknown man. An inquest docket has been opened for investigation.&rdquo;- Zwane said the body of another drowning victim was recovered at Laguna Beach in Durban on Sunday. Lindelani Nxasi (35) went missing while swimming in the early hours of the morning and his body surfaced minutes later. &ldquo;Lifeguards pulled his body out to the shore.&rdquo;- Meanwhile, a case of murder is being investigated by Inanda SAPS after the body of a girl (8) was found dead in a narrow gorge in the area. She was reported missing on Wednesday last week and her relative has been arrested following the gruesome find.Colonel Thembeka Mbhele, KZN cops spokeswoman said: &ldquo;A 48-year-old suspect was arrested for murder. He appeared in the Ntuzuma Magistrates Court on Monday and his case was postponed to 22 February for a formal bail application.&rdquo;